  "intro": "Some Spanish reflexive verbs express changes that English often translates with get. Verbs like ponerse, volverse, hacerse, and quedarse describe different kinds of change.",
  "overview": {
    "body": "Use these reflexive verbs to talk about becoming, getting, or ending up in a new state. The best verb depends on whether the change is temporary, sudden, chosen, gradual, or a final result.",
